Former Manchester United striker, Odion Ighalo, has named Bruno Fernandes as the best player he has played with in his glittering career so far. Ighalo said this when he appeared as a guest on Thursday evening’s edition of Inside The Hive to answer questions from Watford supporters. The 32-year-old played alongside Fernandes during his time at Manchester United during the 2020-2021 season. The Super Eagles attacker made 23 appearances for Man United, scoring five goals during his time at Old Trafford. Asked to name the best player he played with, Ighalo said, “I will say I played with a lot of good players. “I will just say Bruno [Fernandes].”